Package: atesor-ai
Version: @VERSION@
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Akif Ejaz <akif.ejaz@10xengineers.ai>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), docker.io | docker-ce | docker-engine, qemu-user-static, binfmt-support, ca-certificates
Recommends: git
Installed-Size: @SIZE@
Homepage: https://github.com/akifejaz/atesor
Description: Automated C/C++/Go/Rust to RISC-V porting agent
 Atesor AI is a LangGraph multi-agent system that automates porting
 software packages to RISC-V (riscv64). Builds run natively inside an
 Alpine or Debian riscv64 Docker sandbox emulated via QEMU/binfmt_misc.
 .
 The package bundles a self-contained Python virtualenv. It still
 requires a running Docker daemon plus qemu-user-static for riscv64
 emulation, and an LLM API key (GOOGLE_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, or
 OPENROUTER_API_KEY) in the environment or a .env file. See
 /opt/atesor-ai/app/.env-example for all supported variables and
 /opt/atesor-ai/app/BUILD_INFO for the bundled dependency versions.
